enriched.poc.description: Ilan Stern serves as the Chief Investment Officer at 166 2nd, the single family office of WeWork co-founder Adam Neumann, where he leads investment strategy and operations. He previously served as a General Partner and Managing Director at General Catalyst and as a Portfolio Manager at Soros Fund Management, where he managed multi-billion dollar portfolios. Stern began his career in finance at Bear Stearns and Merrill Lynch, and currently sits on the boards of several companies including Flow, FlowCarbon, and Life Biosciences.

enriched.poc.role: Co-founder, Partner and Head of Multi-Family Office
enriched.poc.description: Aksel Azrac is a Co-founder and Senior Partner at 1875 Finance SA, where he leads the Multi-Family Office division. He brings over two decades of experience in wealth management, having previously served on the Executive Board of Banque Ferrier Lullin & Cie and as a fund manager at Banque Paribas (Suisse) SA. He holds degrees from the University of Lausanne and the École Polytechnique Fédérale de Lausanne (EPFL).
